Lamu county commissioner Joseph Kanyiri has ordered a crackdown on and the arrest of those found in possession of crude weapons in public during this electioneering period.The crude weapons include knives, pangas and rungus. Kanyiri on Monday also called for tolerance during the campaigns. He told politicians to preach peace.Kanyiri said the crackdown on crude weapons will ensure individuals with sinister motives that might disrupt peace and coexistence before, during and after the election are nipped in the bud.He said the move will cut down on the increased cases of crude weapon attacks and crime in the county.Kanyiri asked residents and visitors to take the ban seriously. He said police have been ordered to frisk people where necessary in search of the crude weapons.